Linux Workstation Ubuntu 16.04 Desktop
Purpose - To program the PLC

Installation
Follow the instructions here to download the OpenPLC Editor for Linux
https://www.openplcproject.com/plcopen-editor

NOTE - Running the install.sh script does not seem to install all necessary dependencies. 
To fix this, install the missing packages with
'sudo apt-get install python-zeroconf python-lxml python-matplotlib'
'pip2 install six numpy==1.14.6'


In the Ubuntu network settings, add a route to 192.168.90.0 netmask 255.255.255.0 through 192.168.95.1
